This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel meta training and labelling scheme to improve label quality and model accuracy in deep neural networks. The paper also mentions the use of unlabelled data and the generalization power of deep neural networks, which are common topics in the field of machine learning. 

The paper also involves computer vision (cs.CV) as it mentions the use of sensor data and the need for image labelling. Additionally, the paper involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it proposes a new method for improving the accuracy of deep neural networks. 

The paper may also belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it involves the processing of natural language data, which is mentioned in the paper as one of the sources of label errors. 

Finally, the paper may belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it mentions the susceptibility of deep neural networks to label errors, which can have security implications in certain applications.
